# UI Design Expert Rules

## Shared UI First

- Prefer shared components from `@repo/ui` for all UI primitives and patterns.
- If a needed primitive does not exist, add it to `@repo/ui` first, then consume it in apps.
- Use root command `pnpm ui:add <component>` to scaffold shadcn components into `@repo/ui`.

## Theme Consistency

- Use design tokens and theme classes already defined in the system (no random color values).
- Avoid one-off Tailwind styling when an existing shared component variant can solve it.
- Extend component variants in `@repo/ui` instead of introducing app-local visual drift.

## Composition Pattern

- Build app-level components by composing atomic shared components from `@repo/ui`.
- Keep business/domain logic in app components, but keep reusable visual primitives in `@repo/ui`.
- Do not duplicate the same button/card/form primitive separately inside `apps/web`.

## Delivery Checklist

- New UI elements are reusable and exported from `@repo/ui` when broadly applicable.
- App imports shared components via `@repo/ui/components/*`.
- Final UI aligns with the existing theme system and spacing/radius conventions.

## Long Class Names
- Use tailwind utility `cn` on package `@repo/ui` to join long class names to support readability.